(Translated by Google) I eat Vietnamese pho in this restaurant and find a bottle of super glue in it Three weeks ago, I watched a show with my wife at Eighth Avenue in Brooklyn. I went to dinner at 5414 at Eighth Avenue at about half past noon. I ordered a Vietnamese pho, My wife ordered a pork chop rice. When I was half-eaten, I grabbed a bottle of 502 super glue from the noodles. I immediately called the waiter. The waiter thought I would pay for it, but he saw foreign objects in the noodles. I grabbed the noodle from my hand, took it to the back of the kitchen, and then came out and told me that I didn’t need to pay. I said it’s okay. I don’t lack any money for you. . I feel very surprised. Is this happening? Can they say nothing even with an apology?  (Original) I eat Vietnamese pho in this restaurant and find a bottle of super glue in it 三个礼拜前和我妻子在布鲁克林八大道看演出，中午一点半左右到八大道5414去吃饭，我点了一个越南河粉，我妻子点了一份猪扒饭，我吃到一半的时候从面底下捞出一瓶502强力胶，我马上叫服务生过来，服务生以为我要买单，但看到面里有异物，他从我手里抢走面，拿到厨房后面，然后出来跟我说不用买单，我说没关系，我又不缺你这点钱，服务生居然跟我说你们爱怎么样就怎么样，随便你们。我就感觉到很诧异，难道出现这种情况，他们可以连一句道歉点都话都不说吗？
